{
  "name": "RPlog_A_Plea_from_Orson",
  "title": "A Plea from Orson",
  "summary": "In the sunlit clearing of Talon Karrde's base on Myrkr, the Jedi Jessalyn sits among wildflowers puzzling over why the planet's strange field blocks her connection to the Force. The mechanic Orson joins her, and the two share a candid conversation about the wonder and mystery of the Force, revealing how differently Orson now sees the galaxy compared to his employer Karrde. Orson then asks Jessalyn for a favor: on Tatooine he met a woman whose group was chased and crashed by a man on a speederbike while carrying a small inscribed cube she believed could kill millions, an attack he attributes to Cort Stasus, a student of Valak's. The woman lost the cube and three months of memory, and Orson, moved by concern, asks Jessalyn to help her. Recognizing the cube as a likely Sith device akin to a deadly puzzle she once encountered, Jessalyn agrees to meet and aid the woman -- Eva Sargent of FLS on Caspar -- and the two part with a fledgling alliance formed, Orson clumsily leaving her a small wildflower as a token.",
